                        <p> <hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 1.&#8212;<name type="person">Private Martin Schirm</name>, <name type="organization">Co. G, 14th N. Y.
                                Heavy Art'y</name>; age 33; admitted <date type="admit" when="1864-06-15">June 15, 1864</date>, with
                                sunstroke.  Died <date type="death" when="1864-06-22">22d</date>:  <hi rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination: There was much
                                        congestion of the brain with effusion into the ventricles;
                                        the brain-substance was but little softened.&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name type="hospital" key="189">Third Division Hospital</name>, <name type="place">Alexandria, Va.</name></hi> </p>                        
